title: The difference between an influencer and an entrepreneur… #selfimprovement #confidencecoach
caption: false

channel_info.title: Robbie Kramer
channel_info.description:
I'm Robbie Kramer 🎙Host of The Inner Confidence Podcast & Founder of Inner Confidence, Inc.

I lived an exhilarating single life filled with adventures and lessons, and ultimately achieved what I had always aspired to – finding an amazing, feminine, and loving wife. 

I believe my experiences provide a rare balance of wild freedom and committed love, equipping me with the insights to help you navigate the complexities of dating and relationships in today's world. Let me guide you to embrace your desires, improve your social prowess, and ultimately attract the partner who aligns with your highest aspirations.

You won’t find any fluffy, new-age, or cringy stuff here, just tested, proven and actionable advice that yields results.

Apply to join our exclusive Inner Confidence Community of ambitious men who are actively working together to achieve their goals faster   ► https://innerconfidence.com/community

You can email me at robbie@innerconfidence.com with any questions or comments.

transcription: {"text": "People ask me why in my bio, I say entrepreneur, not influencer. I say because there's people out here that are just content creators. They get up in the morning and they're just creating content and they're influencers. I'm an entrepreneur because I've lived many different lives. I've done many different things. I make currency many different ways, but I have an influence. If you're doing your job well as an entrepreneur, you clearly have influence. You have the ability to get people to follow whatever you're working on. People really haven't broken it down. Are you an influencer or do you have influence? Which one? It's a good distinction to make. Yeah, like if you have influence, you have the ability to master your craft and become something so great. But you're looking at Instagram, TikTok and all this stuff and you're seeing people making easy money just from their iPhones and that's what you want to do. You see what I'm saying?
